HEADWORD: Falderal
<hw>Fal"de*ral`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Nonsense; foolish talk.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>folderol</asp> and <asp>falderol</asp>.]</altsp>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> humbug; balderdash; poppycock.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a knickknack; a gew-gaw.</def>⟦br⟧
